{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd88ba0e94a3c4025d3c", "type": "numerical", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "<p>In a double slit experiment shown in figure, when light of wavelength <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>nm</mi></math> is used, dark fringe is observed at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>. If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>,\u00a0the minimum distance between the slits <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>\u00a0and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>\u00a0is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>. Write the value of\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi>\u03b1</mi></math>\u00a0to the nearest integer.</p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/db11ceee-3588-4622-97d4-6541cebc69d4.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 210px;\"/>", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "2", "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/db11ceee-3588-4622-97d4-6541cebc69d4.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 210px;\"/></p><p>According to the given diagram, the path difference for minima at P is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u2206</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>D</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And, from the condition of minima, it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u2206</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equations (1) and (2) imply that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msqrt><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>D</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>D</mi><mi>\u03bb</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>D</mi><mi>\u03bb</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>\u03bb</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>14</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2248</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mo>\u2234</mo><mi>d</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>20</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>mm</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Therefore,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ84703210", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba3"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c01d30997d3436bb00", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": 2, "numericalUpperLimit": 2, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e